ited%20States%20and%20Canada%20will%20witness%20the%20Moon%20completely%20obscure%20the%20Sun's%20light%2C%20a%20rare%20celestial%20spectacle%20that%20won't%20be%20visible%20for%20most%20of%20North%20America%20again%20until%202044.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedical%20literature%20is%20teeming%20with%20examples%20of%20people%20who%20suffered%20damage%20to%20their%20retinas%20--%20the%20layer%20of%20light-sensitive%20tissue%20at%20the%20back%20of%20the%20eye%20--%20and%20health%20professionals%20are%20offering%20advice%20on%20how%20to%20avoid%20becoming%20the%20next%20cautionary%20tale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAaron%20Zimmerman%2C%20a%20clinical%20professor%20of%20optometry%20at%20the%20Ohio%20State%20University%2C%20told%20AFP%20that%20the%20dangers%20of%20sungazing%20during%20eclipses%20were%20discussed%20by%20the%20ancient%20Greek%20philosopher%20Socrates%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20until%20recently%20that%20science%20really%20caught%20up%20with%20how%20eye%20injury%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20eclipses%2C%20he%20explained%2C%20the%20main%20damage%20comes%20from%20%26quot%3Bphotochemical%20toxicity%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20short%2C%20high-energy%20wavelengths%20of%20light%20--%20blues%2C%20violets%20and%20non-visible%20ultraviolets%20--%20trigger%20chemical%20reactions%20that%20damage%20the%20rods%20and%20cones%20of%20the%20retina.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECue%20visits%20to%20the%20emergency%20department%20by%20people%20with%20complaints%20of%20blurry%20vision%2C%20changes%20in%20color%20perception%2C%20and%20blind%20spots%2C%20with%20the%20outlook%20for%20recovery%20far%20from%20certain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuman%20beings%20inherently%20look%20away%20from%20the%20Sun%20because%20of%20the%20discomfort%20it%20causes%2C%20but%20during%20eclipses%20%26quot%3Byou%20can%20psychologically%20override%26quot%3B%20that%20instinct%2C%20explained%20Zimmerman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20famous%20journal%20report%20about%20the%202017%20US%20solar%20eclipse%20involved%20a%20woman%20in%20her%20twenties%20who%20presented%20to%20the%20New%20York%20Eye%20and%20Ear%20Infirmary%20after%20looking%20at%20the%20solar%20rim%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20times%20for%20approximately%206%20seconds%20without%20protective%20glasses%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20later%20with%20eclipse%20glasses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHours%20later%2C%20objects%20started%20to%20look%20fuzzy%20and%20out%20of%20shape%2C%20colors%20became%20distorted%2C%20and%20she%20developed%20a%20central%20black%20spot%20in%20her%20left%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20advanced%20imaging%20technique%20was%20able%20to%20show%20the%20damage%20at%20the%20cellular%20level%20which%20persisted%20on%20her%20follow%20up%20six%20weeks%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Permanent%20blank%20spot'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYoung%20adults%20might%20be%20more%20susceptible%2C%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20paper%20said%2C%20because%20of%20larger%20pupils%2C%20clearer%20eye%20structure%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bpoorer%20recognition%20of%20the%20dangers%26quot%3B%20of%20viewing%20eclipses%20with%20improper%20eyewear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20some%20cases%2C%20it's%20just%20partially%20damaged%20and%20it%20may%20resolve%20so%20that%20you%20don't%20notice%20it%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20Neil%20Bressler%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20ophthalmology%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%20and%20editor-in-chief%20of%20JAMA%20Ophthalmology%20told%20AFP.%20If%20recovery%20happens%2C%20it's%20normally%20within%20the%20first%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20in%20other%20cases%2C%20it%20can%20leave%20a%20permanent%20blank%20spot...%20and%20we%20don't%20have%20a%20treatment%20to%20reverse%20that.%20It's%20like%20brain%20tissue%2C%20once%20you%20lose%20it%2C%20it%20won't%20grow%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Bressler.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20view%20the%20eclipse%20is%20with%20eclipse%20sunglasses%2C%20which%20block%20out%2099.999%20percent%20of%20light.%20Always%20go%20for%20genuine%20products.%20To%20test%20if%20your%20glasses%20are%20up%20to%20standard%2C%20%26quot%3Bfind%20the%20brightest%20light%20bulb%20in%20your%20home%20--%20and%20then%20look%20at%20that%20from%20up%20close%20and%20you%20should%20barely%20be%20able%20to%20see%20the%20light%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zimmerman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20it's%20too%20late%20to%20procure%20specialist%20eyewear%2C%20then%20there%20are%20indirect%20methods%2C%20such%20as%20punching%20a%20pinhole%20into%20a%20cardboard%20and%20letting%20the%20light%20shine%20onto%20another%20surface%2C%20or%20even%20using%20the%20humble%20kitchen%20colander%20to%20the%20same%20effect.%20NASA's%20webcast%20is%20another%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20fortunate%20enough%20to%20be%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bpath%20of%20totality%2C%26quot%3B%20under%20which%20the%20Moon%20will%20fully%20block%20out%20the%20Sun%2C%20can%20look%20up%20without%20glasses%20and%20admire%20the%20Sun's%20outer%20atmosphere%2C%20or%20corona%2C%20glowing%20from%20behind%20the%20silhouette%20of%20the%20Moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20said%20Bressler%2C%20the%20danger%20is%20not%20having%20protection%20before%20and%20after%20those%20precious%20moments%2C%20which%20can%20last%20anywhere%20from%20seconds%20to%20a%20few%20minutes%2C%20depending%20on%20your%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20must%20know%20when%20it%20begins%20and%20use%20protection%20before%20that%2C%20and%20you%20may%20be%20enamored%20by%20looking%20at%20all%20this%2C%20but%20you%20must%20have%20some%20alarm%20to%20tell%20you%20it's%20about%20to%20end%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712542800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fcvldvlj8_solar-eclipse-representational-pixabay_625x300_08_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22htt