r%20grocery%20store%20inventory%20and%20purchases.%20The%20company%20aims%20to%20%26quot%3Beliminate%20food%20waste%20and%20make%20nutritious%20food%20more%20accessible%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.afresh.com%2Fresources%2Fannouncing-115-million-series-b-funding-round-for-afresh%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO%20Matt%20Schwartz%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.winnowsolutions.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWinnow%3C%2Fa%3E%20takes%20a%20similar%20approach%20to%20restaurants.%20The%20company%20installs%20cameras%20above%20garbage%20bins%2C%20which%20AI%20then%20monitors%20to%20assess%20what%20food%20is%20going%20to%20waste%20and%20how%20much%20is%20discarded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20data%20in%20hand%2C%20restaurants%20can%20shift%20to%20smaller%20portions%20of%20the%20food%20that's%20getting%20trashed.%20Or%20even%20remove%20those%20items%20from%20the%20menu%20altogether.%20The%20company%20says%20it%20has%20helped%20restaurant%20kitchens%20slash%20their%20purchasing%20costs%20by%20up%20to%208%25%20by%20monitoring%20garbage%20and%20tackling%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20food%20waste%20problem%20is%20real%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20growing%20global%20population%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20surpass%209%20billion%20by%202050.%20People%20living%20in%20poverty%20are%20spending%2050%25%20to%2080%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20food%20alone%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Ftopics%2Fchemicals-and-pollution-action%2Fcircularity-sectors%2Ffood-and-food-waste%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFood%2520loss%2520and%2520waste%2520%25E2%2580%2593%2520roughly%2Cto%2520be%2520overweight%2520or%2520obese.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20Environment%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20reducing%20food%20waste%20could%20reduce%20pressure%20on%20water%20supplies%20and%20lower%20deforestation%2C%20the%20agency%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%